@startuml
title Manage Personalized Alert Subscriptions

actor "City Operator" as Operator
participant "Manage Alert\nSubscriptions" as MAS
participant "Alerting\nManagement" as AM
database "Alert\nSubscriptions DB" as DB

== View Current Subscription ==

Operator -> MAS : Open Subscription Settings
MAS -> AM : Request Current Preferences
AM -> DB : Query Subscription (userId)
DB --> AM : Subscription or null
AM --> MAS : Display Current Preferences
MAS --> Operator : Show Metric Types, Zones, Min Severity

== Update Subscription ==

Operator -> MAS : Select Metrics, Zones, Severity
MAS -> AM : Submit Updated Preferences
AM -> AM : Validate Selections
AM -> DB : Upsert Subscription
DB --> AM : Subscription Saved
AM --> MAS : Send Confirmation
MAS --> Operator : Confirm Subscriptions Updated

== Alert Filtering (Subsequent Alerts) ==

note over AM, DB
  When a new alert is created, the Dispatcher
  knowledge source loads subscriptions from DB,
  calls find_subscribers(), and only notifies
  operators whose preferences match the alert's
  metric type, zone, and severity.
end note

@enduml
